{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place milk and egg yolks in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>4 min\/80°C\/speed 6<\/nobr>.","Add sugar and cream then cook <nobr>2 min\/80°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Pour mixture, up to 4 cm deep, into shallow freezer-proof containers and leave to cool for 30 minutes. Refrigerate for 12 hours to allow mixture to mature then place in freezer until solid (approx. 10 hours).","Before serving, remove ice cream from freezer and cut into 3 cm chunks. Place ice cream chunks in mixing bowl and churn <nobr>30 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>- <strong>9<\/strong> while stirring with spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Add strawberries and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Serve immediately or freeze until required."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["300 g whole milk","4 egg yolks, from large eggs","65 g caster sugar","210 g clotted cream (55 % fat)","200 - 250 g fresh strawberries, hulled, cut in pieces (1-2 cm)"]}],"id":"r95370","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-vb3jz4zw0Bc\/XZaot8VW9NI\/AAAAAAAAhM8\/Hu_C85YKFeQ9EUPq_pjMDkrwnvCgpEbdACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_vhOePH89ecH7Me08.png","title":"Clotted Cream and Strawberry Ice Cream","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.9 g","fat":"21.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"12.4 g","calories":"1069 kJ \/ 256 kcal"},"usefulItems":"freezer-proof containers, long sharp knife, freezer, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Inspired by the traditional Devonshire cream tea, this summery variation using the ingredients of this English classic works perfectly served in a cone, accompanied by a strawberry sauce or coulis."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","24h","8 portions"]}